narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Take if you need to for your credits or if you want to vastly improve your Spanish grammar and speaking.

You'll take this class if you need to. I don't feel I became any better at Spanish, but I did actually enjoy class time with Prfa Leon. She didn't bog us down with busy work and there was lots of chatting.

Spanish 140 03 focuses much more on practical applications of Spanish than Spanish 130. The course materials were much more interesting and the amount of time spent on textbook work as compared to supplementary materials was much smaller.
Pretty much the same as L3 but more assessments
